Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

AS TO COUNT 1 AS ORALLY AMENDED TO OBSTRUCTING AN OFFICER.

The Court ordered defendant to serve 30 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 7 (seven) days time served, The Court granted Huber privileges, pursuant to 303.08 Wis. Stats. for work and CGIP program ONLY: Report date: May 15, 2015 by 5:00 p.m. 

Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs, fees and surcharges (included DNA surcharge) by November 12, 2015, or to be docketed as a civil judgment.

